From 5cdcf51c516647674e874f3bda8bb872c42aa584 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 23:46:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] inline-3d(#22): DP-composited 2D overlays + coherent
 whole-window present
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

browser#22 Option B — move the 2D-over-3D composite into the display processor
and present the woven output whole-window so 2D chrome spanning tile gaps is
single-sourced (kills the sticky-header seam double the per-tile present had).

Seams A/B/C (DP overlay atlas):
- Sync vendored XR_DXR_weave.h to SPEC 5.
- DisplayXRWeaveClient / DisplayXRWeaveGpu / DisplayXRWeaveProvider: assemble a
  window-sized premul-RGBA overlay atlas from inline_3d_overlays_ and stage it as
  the batch overlay input (SetBatchOverlay), chained on the last chunk's submit.
- skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu WeaveCompositedSurface: build the atlas
  (kSrcOver into a scratch SharedImage), ProduceOverlayForWeave, stage before
  SubmitBatchSync; delete the browser-side kSrcOver draw-back.

B1 whole-window present (v5 firstChunk):
- SubmitBatchWin sets XrWeaveSubmitInfoDXR::firstChunk = (done == 0) so the
  runtime clears its woven output to transparent on the frame's first chunk
  (correct for single-submit frames and the >MAX-rect chunk loop).
- WeaveCompositedSurface phase (B): replace the per-tile displayxr_drawn_rect_[i]
  kSrc draw-back with ONE whole-window kSrcOver of the woven output
  (displayxr_shared_woven_size_ ∩ window_bounds, NEAREST) — opaque tiles replace
  the page, transparent gaps show it through, DP-composited overlays on top.

Validated on real Leia (runtime v5 g875971038 + this build): wall-3d clean —
crisp 2D overlays, 3D woven tiles, no seam double.
